itemDescription: British soldier and politician and Governor of Bombay and Bengal (1894-1939)

wikipedia_page.main: Michael Herbert Rudolf Knatchbull, 5th Baron Brabourne,  (8 May 1895 – 23 February 1939) was a British peer and soldier, the son of the 4th Baron Brabourne.

response: * February 23 – Michael Knatchbull, 5th Baron Brabourne, British peer, soldier (b. 1895)

link_mentions.page: Order of the Crown of India
response: *1937: The Lady Brabourne (wife of Michael Knatchbull, 5th Baron Brabourne, Governor of the Presidency of Bombay, 1931–1937, and of Bengal, 1937–1939)

Brabourne was born in 1924, the second son of Michael Knatchbull, 5th Baron Brabourne and his wife, Lady Doreen Knatchbull. He was educated at Eton College and Brasenose College, Oxford. He was barely 14 when his father died in February 1939 and his elder brother, Norton, inherited the Barony.
